features: [Ample Storage for Any Room] With six 11.8" x 29.1" open shelves, this 11.8"D x 31.5"W x 73.2"H storage shelf offers plenty of storage to display your favorite books, decorations, and plants in the living room, bedroom, bathroom, or entryway

[Stable and Safe] X-shaped bars reinforce the structure, adjustable feet keep this tall book shelf balanced on slightly uneven floors, and the included anti-tip kit will help you fix it to the wall for greater stability and safety

[Embrace an Industrial Vibe] The rustic brown shelves paired with a black steel frame create a stylish industrial look, allowing this freestanding shelf to fit seamlessly in with your home decor and give your space an instant update

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars can I say so cute!!?
reviews.reviewText: It was SOO adorable! I had it when I was living in my first apartment, in my living room- prior to moving it in my bedroom before my big move across the country! Still holding beautifully to this day!! My sister has it now! She loves it!!! Absolutely beautiful and well put together! All the pieces came with it and it maybe took me about an hour to put together! VERY EASY!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very sterdy and nice for the price
reviews.reviewText: Didn't think it would be this good but honestly pretty sterdy and not too bad too look at. Also has good space for items and holds a good amount of weight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Loved the first so much I bought another!
reviews.reviewText: These look great! Semi-easy to build just by myself (although it suggests two people). There is a little wonkiness I noticed on the back crossbars both times I purchased this, as they bow out, but maybe they are intended to be flexible? Either way it doesn't look like it's defective and the shelves are nice and sturdy. I just have them pulled out from the wall about an inch as to not scratch them. Still giving these 5 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for the money
reviews.reviewText: These bookshelves are pretty nice for how much they cost. They were dead simple to assemble. The one complaint I would have is that they aren't the sturdiest on carpet. Now we didn't anchor them into the wall, which I'm sure would help, and they do provide tools for that in the packaging. But, if you were thinking you might be able to avoid putting holes in your walls, I might think twice. The bottom support legs are pretty small and don't provide a great surface on the carpet, but I think they'd be fine on hard floors. Overall, though, pretty good pieces.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Purchased for Tiny House
reviews.reviewText: I own a 540 sq ft Tiny House. While the upper walls of the interior of my house have built-in shelves instead of cabinets, there were areas that were impractical for built-in shelves due to the electrical wiring running inside the walls. I opted for these bookshelves and am very satisfied. They are attractive, sturdy, and fit in odd areas where built-in shelves aren't practical. I ended up purchasing 4 units - two this size and two narrower units. I definitely recommend these units and a large unit for hanging clothing with open-work side storage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This was so easy to set up. The shelves hold a lot and it is very durable. Easy to move around.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for some of my craft supplies and miscellaneous things. It was super easy to put together, and took me less than an hour. The instructions are simple and easy to follow. No blemishes or scratches in shipment. The shelves are very sturdy, and I love the ample amount of space between each shelf. 10/10 recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful & good quality
reviews.reviewText: This book shelf was a little time consuming to put together, but it was so worth it! It’s great quality and I am going to order a second one.

I expected the wood to be a bit lighter because it is in the pictures but I'm absolutely in love with the darker brown! It was easy to assemble and took me maybe an hour, its nice and sturdy. I didn't use the wall hooks but it seems to be doing fine with my cat jumping on it and bumping it!
The price is reasonable but could be better but other than that, fantastic quality, takes about a half hour to assemble and very sturdy.
Love this bookshelf, I bought 2 to put in a corner, they look great! So happy I found these after looking for many weeks! Easy to put together too

La instalación es super rapida y sencilla, lo armé en 45 min! Tenía la premura de entrar a una junta por telefono y en lo que estaba en casa esperando me di a la tarea de armarlo, claro que previamente ya habia leido el instructivo. Por cierto, ya viene incluida la herramienta para armarlo que es una llave tipo L con cabeza hexagonal pero yo use un destornillador con matraca y fue mas sencillo.Por otro lado, los acabados son de primera, esta muy bien pintado y alineado. Pienso en comprar otro para ponerlo esquinado con el actual.

One of the base metal pieces is crooked which required me to bend it using a hammer, screwdriver and cloth. Even then the metal halves weren't straight but rather quite scewed. Once you screw the shelves in place it bends it mostly straight as the metal is fairly malliable. Overall I like the look and felt assembly was reasonably easy but the quality of manufacturing certainly leaves something to be desired. Pro tip pay attention to where the screw holes are on the back where the cross sections mount. This will avoid having to disassemble / reassemble to swap bar placements. It's what I was looking for so I'm satisfied but having to repair something you bought was frustrating.
